schedule:
Week 1: Introduction to MCDM;
Week 2: Structuring unknown decision scenarios using Decision-Making Trial and Evaluation Laboratory;
Week 3: Decision analysis using Quality Function Deployment;
Week 4: Optimum Selection using Analytic Hierarchy Process and Analytic Network Process;
Week 5: Measuring Attractiveness by a Category-Based Evaluation Technique;
Week 6: The concept of Fuzzy set theory and Fuzzy Inference Systems;
Week 7: Group decision-making using Preference Ranking Organization Method for Enrichment Evaluation and the Technique for Order of Preference by Similarity to Ideal Solution;
Week 8: Peer evaluation using Data Envelopment Analysis;
Week 9: Term project - proposal presentation;
Week 10: Modeling I;
Week 11: Modeling II;
Week 12: Simplex method;
Week 13: Big M method;
Week 14: Dual analysis;
Week 15: Final evaluation; 
Week 16: Term project - final presentation;
